Is Labor Day a paid holiday at Amazon?

2025-08-29T13:29:44.394698Z system

2025-08-29T13:29:44.496441Z assistant

Yes for Amazon U.S. fulfillment center and operations employees, Labor Day is one of the six paid holidays recognized each year.

Those six are:

  • New Years Day
  • Memorial Day
  • Independence Day
  • Labor Day
  • Thanksgiving Day
  • Christmas Day

How it usually works:

  • If youre scheduled off, youll typically receive holiday pay (8 hours).
  • If youre scheduled to work, youll usually receive time-and-a-half pay (1.5x) in addition to your holiday pay.
  • Some sites add extra overtime multipliers if you work beyond your shift on a holiday, but the baseline is 1.5x.

Since youre at TPA4 RME, it should follow the standard U.S. Ops policy but note that local leadership sometimes sends reminders with site-specific clarifications.
